\\n  var monthDays \\u003d [31, isLeapYear ? 29 : 28, 31, 30, 31, 30, 31, 31, 30, 31, 30, 31];\\n  var month \\u003d 0;  \\n  for (var i \\u003d 0; i \\u003c monthDays.length; i++) {\\n    if provides the following functionality:\\n\\n**Features:**\\n- Extracts JWT tokens from Authorization Bearer headers or custom input\\n- Decodes header, payload, signature, or full token\\n- Supports extracting specific claims with dot notation (e.g., \\\"user.profile.name\\\")\\n- Optional JSON string output for objects\\n- Comprehensive error handling and logging\\n\\n**Usage Examples:**\\n1. **Extract user ID from token:** Set Extract Part to \\\"Specific Claim\\\" and Claim Name to \\\"sub\\\"\\n2. **Get full payload:** Set Extract Part to \\\"Payload/Claims\\\" \\n3. **Check token type:** Set Extract Part to \\\"Header\\\" to see algorithm and type\\n4. **Get expiration time:** Set Extract Part to \\\"Specific Claim\\\" and Claim Name to \\\"exp\\\"\\n\\n**Important Notes:**\\n- This template only DECODES JWTs - it does NOT verify signatures\\n- For production use, implement proper JWT signature verification\\n- Uses only sandboxed sGTM APIs (fromBase64, JSON.parse, etc.)\\n- Returns undefined if token is invalid or missing\\n- Supports nested claim extraction (e.g., \\\"user.profile.email\\\")\\n\\n**Security Considerations:**\\n- JWT tokens contain sensitive information\\n- Always use HTTPS in production\\n- Consider token expiration (exp claim)\\n- Implement proper error handling in your tags\\n\\n\\n\"\n      },\n      {\n
